== Aitsu_Service_Google_Geocode ==

The Aitsu_Service_Google_Geocode class requests the Google Geolocation API and
persists the result. If there is a cached result not exceeding the specifed age
the cache is used.

A typical usage looks like:

Aitsu_Service_Google_Geocode :: getInstance()->locate('brunnmattstrasse 13, thörishaus, schweiz')

or - if you would like to overrule the cache...

Aitsu_Service_Google_Geocode :: getInstance()->locate('brunnmattstrasse 13, thörishaus, schweiz', 0)

The locate method return a standard object with the id, lat and lng as its members.